==English==

===Etymology===
Shortened from elaboratory; confer {{OF.}} ''elaboratoire'', {{F.}} ''laboratoire''; from {{L.}} ''laboratorium'' from ''laborare'' (to labour'')

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''laboratory'''  (''plural:'' laboratories)
# a [[room]], [[building]] or [[institution]] [[equipped]] for [[scientific]] [[research]], [[experimentation]] or [[analysis]]
# a place where [[chemical]]s, [[drug]]s or [[microbe]]s are [[prepared]] or [[manufactured]]

